import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import { Account } from '../../components/Account'
const account = {
      address: '0xabc',
      balance: '300000000000000000',
    }
let accountPicker = () => {
  return false // We don't need this to do anything in the storybook context
}

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"account"}}><MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="h1" props={{"aria-hidden":true,"href":"#account"}}><MDXTag name="span" components={components} parentName="a" props={{"className":"icon-link"}}>{`#`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>{`Account`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"account-1"}}><MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="h2" props={{"aria-hidden":true,"href":"#account-1"}}><MDXTag name="span" components={components} parentName="a" props={{"className":"icon-link"}}>{`#`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>{`Account`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __position={0} __code={`<Account showAccountPicker={accountPicker} account={account} />`} __scope={{props,Account}}>
    <Account showAccountPicker={accountPicker} account={account} />
</Playground></MDXTag>
